---
import { MetaHarnessLayers } from '@metaharness/animations';
import VizSurface from '../../VizSurface.astro';
---

<section
  id="answer"
  class="border-y border-neutral-200 bg-neutral-100/60 px-6 py-24 md:py-32 dark:border-neutral-900 dark:bg-neutral-900/40"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 sm:text-5xl dark:text-neutral-50"
      >
        The answer: meta-harnesses
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl">
      <p
        class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300"
      >
        A meta-harness is the layer above AI agent harnesses like Claude Code
        and Codex. It spans repositories, sessions, and time: coordinating
        cross-repo work, persisting memory between sessions, and enforcing
        policy, so agentic work connects and compounds instead of resetting
        with every session.
      </p>
      <p
        class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300"
      >
        You have seen this move before. React gave you the core, and you chose
        the router, the data-fetching library, the component library, and
        stitched them together yourself. It worked, and it did not transfer:
        every team rebuilt the same setup differently. Then Next.js and TanStack
        packaged the proven choices into a meta-framework which made React apps
        faster and more stable to build.
      </p>
      <p
        class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300"
      >
        A meta-harness makes the same move around your harness. It fills the
        gaps with proven solutions to support your workflow.{' '}
        <mark>Your agent gets more capable, more autonomous and you get more
          productive.</mark>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="-mx-6 mt-14 max-w-5xl min-w-0 md:mx-auto">
      <VizSurface aspect="aspect-[3/2]">
        <MetaHarnessLayers
          client:visible
          harnessPreBuilt
          playOnce
          width={900}
          height={600}
          className="mx-auto"
        />
      </VizSurface>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
